President Obama issued a statement wishing Coptic Orthodox Christians a joyous Christmas. He emphasized the importance of the messages of peace and hope that have endured for over 2,000 years since the birth of Jesus. The President reaffirmed the United States' commitment to protecting Christians and people of faith in Egypt and globally. He stated that the freedom to practice one's faith is crucial for stable and thriving societies, and the US will remain vigilant in safeguarding this freedom. The President extended his blessings to Coptic Christians and joined them in praying for peace in the coming year.